# 🌍 City Tour Website & Weather Dashboard\n\n![City Tour](https://img.shields.io/badge/City%20Tour-Website-blue)\n![Weather Dashboard](https://img.shields.io/badge/Weather-Dashboard-green)\n![License](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-yellow)\n![Status](https://img.shields.io/badge/Status-Live-success)\n\n## 📚 Overview\n\nA comprehensive web application featuring:\n- **City Tour Website** - Explore amazing cities with curated tour packages\n- **Weather Dashboard** - Real-time weather data and forecasts for any city worldwide\n\n## 🚀 Live Demos\n\n- **City Tour**: [View Website](https://github.com/dhwanihakanice-crypto/city-tour-website)\n- **Weather Dashboard**: [View Dashboard](https://github.com/dhwanihakanice-crypto/city-tour-website)\n- **GitHub Pages**: Coming soon!\n\n## ✨ Features\n\n### 🏙️ City Tour Website\n- Browse featured city tours (Paris, Tokyo, New York, London, Barcelona, Rome)\n- Detailed tour information with pricing\n- Beautiful responsive design\n- Smooth scrolling navigation\n- Contact form\n- Tour booking modal\n\n### 🌤️ Weather Dashboard\n- Real-time weather for any city\n- Geolocation support (get weather for your current location)\n- Hourly forecast (next 12 hours)\n- 5-day forecast\n- Save favorite cities\n- Detailed weather metrics (humidity, wind speed, pressure, etc.)\n- Beautiful emoji weather icons\n- Mobile-responsive design\n- Error handling\n\n## 📋 Project Structure\n\n```\ncity-tour-website/\n├── index.html                    # City Tour main page\n├── weather-dashboard.html        # Weather Dashboard main page\n├── styles.css                    # City Tour styling\n├── app.js                        # City Tour functionality\n├── weather-dashboard/\n│   ├── styles.css               # Weather Dashboard styling\n│   ├── app.js                   # Weather Dashboard functionality\n│   ├── README.md                # Weather Dashboard setup guide\n│   └── .env.example             # Environment variables template\n├── DEPLOYMENT.md                # Deployment guide\n├── package.json                 # Node.js dependencies\n├── server.js                    # Express server (optional)\n└── README.md                    # This file\n```\n\n## 🛠️ Technologies Used\n\n### Frontend\n- HTML5\n- CSS3 (with CSS Grid & Flexbox)\n- Vanilla JavaScript (ES6+)\n- LocalStorage API\n- Geolocation API\n\n### Backend (Optional)\n- Node.js\n- Express.js\n- Axios\n- CORS\n- dotenv\n\n### APIs\n- OpenWeatherMap API (free tier)\n\n## 📦 Installation\n\n### Prerequisites\n- Modern web browser\n- OpenWeatherMap API key (free: https://openweathermap.org/api)\n\n### Quick Start (No Server Required)\n\n1. **Clone the repository**\n   ```bash\n   git clone https://github.com/dhwanihakanice-crypto/city-tour-website.git\n   cd city-tour-website\n   ```\n\n2. **Add OpenWeatherMap API Key**\n   - Open `weather-dashboard/app.js`\n   - Replace `const API_KEY = 'YOUR_OPENWEATHERMAP_API_KEY'` with your actual key\n\n3. **Open in Browser**\n   - City Tour: Open `index.html` in your browser\n   - Weather Dashboard: Open `weather-dashboard.html` in your browser\n\n### Setup with Server\n\n1. **Install Dependencies**\n   ```bash\n   npm install\n   ```\n\n2. **Create .env file**\n   ```bash\n   cp weather-dashboard/.env.example .env\n   # Edit .env and add your API key\n   ```\n\n3. **Start Server**\n   ```bash\n   npm start\n   # Server runs on http://localhost:3000\n   ```\n\n## 🌐 Deployment Options\n\n### ⭐ Recommended: GitHub Pages (FREE)\n\n1. Go to repository Settings → Pages\n2. Select \"Deploy from a branch\" → main branch\n3. Save\n4. Your site will be live at: `https://dhwanihakanice-crypto.github.io/city-tour-website/`\n\n### Other Hosting Options\n- **Netlify**: https://netlify.com\n- **Vercel**: https://vercel.com\n- **Heroku**: https://heroku.com\n- **AWS Amplify**: https://aws.amazon.com/amplify/\n\n**📖 See [DEPLOYMENT.md](DEPLOYMENT.md) for detailed instructions for all platforms**\n\n## 🎯 API Configuration\n\n### OpenWeatherMap API\n\n**Free Tier Includes:**\n- Current weather data\n- 5-day forecast\n- 60 calls/minute\n- 1,000,000 calls/month\n\n**Get Your Key:**\n1. Visit https://openweathermap.org/api\n2. Sign up for free account\n3. Generate API key\n4. Add to your app\n\n## 📱 Responsive Design\n\n- ✅ Desktop (1200px+)\n- ✅ Tablet (768px - 1199px)\n- ✅ Mobile (< 768px)\n- ✅ Small Mobile (< 480px)\n\n## 🔧 Customization\n\n### Change Colors\nEdit CSS variables in:\n- `styles.css` (City Tour)\n- `weather-dashboard/styles.css` (Weather)\n\n```css\n:root {\n    --primary-color: #2563eb;\n    --secondary-color: #1e40af;\n    /* ... more variables ... */\n}\n```\n\n### Change Temperature Unit\nIn `weather-dashboard/app.js`:\n```javascript\n// Metric (Celsius) - default\nunits=metric\n\n// Imperial (Fahrenheit)\nunits=imperial\n\n// Kelvin\nunits=standard\n```\n\n### Add More Tours\nEdit the `tours` array in `app.js`:\n```javascript\nconst tours = [\n    {\n        id: 1,\n        name: 'Your City',\n        emoji: '🏙️',\n        description: 'Description...',\n        price: 99.99,\n        // ... more properties\n    }\n];\n```\n\n## 📊 Features Roadmap\n\n- [ ] User authentication\n- [ ] Booking system with payments\n- [ ] User reviews and ratings\n- [ ] Multi-language support\n- [ ] Dark mode toggle\n- [ ] Advanced weather alerts\n- [ ] Weather maps integration\n- [ ] PDF export for tours\n- [ ] Email notifications\n- [ ] Admin dashboard\n\n## 🐛 Known Issues\n\nNone currently. Please report issues via GitHub Issues.\n\n## 🧪 Testing\n\n### Local Testing\n```bash\n# Using Python\npython -m http.server 8000\n# or\npython3 -m http.server 8000\n\n# Using Node.js\nnpx http-server\n\n# Visit: http://localhost:8000\n```\n\n### Test Checklist\n- [ ] City search works\n- [ ] Weather displays correctly\n- [ ] Geolocation functions\n- [ ] Save/remove cities works\n- [ ] Responsive on mobile\n- [ ] No console errors\n- [ ] API calls successful\n\n## 📚 Documentation\n\n- [City Tour README](./RE